The '''''Writing Magazine''''' issue of August 2014 includes the article "Tolkien on writing and me" by Paula Coston (pp.&nbsp;12–14). The article is about:

{{blockquote|a series of letters between [[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien]] and Paula Coston née Iley on writing. Paula had links with Tolkien because her grand-parents lived next door to him, and she met him and [[Edith Tolkien|Edith]] as a child.|<ref>{{webcite|author=Trotter|articleurl=http://www.tolkienguide.com/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?topic_id=2242|articlename=Possible unpublished Tolkien letter|dated=|website=Guide|accessed=6 July 2014}}</ref>}}

The article contains quotations from and reproductions of the letters ([[Letter to Paula Coston (6 January 1969)|Paula Coston (6 January 1969)]] and [[Letter to Paula Coston (26 August 1965)|Paula Coston (26 August 1965)]]).<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.tolkiensociety.org/2014/07/series-of-tolkiens-letters-published/|articlename=Series of Tolkien’s letters published|dated=6 July 2014|website=TS|accessed=6 July 2014}}</ref>

